DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$f0 = random(2,8,1);
$f1 = random(2,8,1);
$f1++ if ( $f1 == $f0 );

$fp1 = random(2,8,1);

$val = $fp1 - $f1 + $f0;

TEXT(beginproblem());
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Let \( f \) be twice differentiable with
\( f(0)=$f0 \),  \( f(1)=$f1 \), and \( f'(1)=$fp1 \).
Evaluate the integral
\( \int^{1}_{0} xf''(x)dx \).

$PAR
\( \int^{1}_{0} xf''(x)dx = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( Compute( $val )->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Using integration by parts we have
\[
\int^{1}_{0} xf''(x)dx = xf'(x)\bigg|^{1}_{0} - \int^{1}_{0} f'(x)dx
\]
\[
= 1\cdot f'(1) - 0\cdot f'(0) - [f(1) - f(0)]
\]
\[
= $fp1 - 0 - $f1 + $f0 = $val.
\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
